      • getLanguageFromPaymentDataOrFallback

        protected static java.lang.String getLanguageFromPaymentDataOrFallback​(CreatePaymentData cpd)
        Try to define payment locale (two characters ISO 639) in the next order:
        • from custom payment data config, e.g. cpd.getConfigByName(LANGUAGE_CODE) (if not null)
        • else try CreatePaymentMethodBase.getLanguageFromCart(Cart) with cpd.getCart()
        • else fallback to "en" locale
        Parameters:
        cpd - payment-cart data from which define the locale
        Returns:
        non-null 2 characters string language name according to ISO 639 format
        See Also:
        CreatePaymentMethodBase.getLanguageFromCart(Cart)
